1
00:00:00,410 --> 00:00:01,410
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,470 --> 00:00:03,480
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,540 --> 00:00:05,240
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,280 --> 00:00:09,010
Welcome, Director Kim.

5
00:00:09,110 --> 00:00:10,580
I mean, President Kim.

6
00:00:11,650 --> 00:00:13,180
Nice of you to finally show up.

7
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:14,790
That whole mess was ages ago.

8
00:00:15,950 --> 00:00:16,960
I apologize.

9
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,460
I was held up by something
at the office.

10
00:00:20,390 --> 00:00:22,060
We heard about it on the news.

11
00:00:22,760 --> 00:00:24,400
You must be so devastated.

12
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:26,060
Devastated? Please.

13
00:00:26,530 --> 00:00:28,300
She's not the one
who had her engagement called off.

14
00:00:29,170 --> 00:00:32,140
I wanted to talk to Ms. Choi
about the wedding,

15
00:00:33,170 --> 00:00:35,270
but she must've left early
since she wasn't at her desk.

16
00:00:36,040 --> 00:00:39,140
Really? She hasn't come home yet.

17
00:00:39,240 --> 00:00:40,550
Let me give her a call.

18
00:00:40,980 --> 00:00:41,980
In that case,

19
00:00:43,480 --> 00:00:46,420
do you mind if I wait in her room
until she gets back?

20
00:00:47,090 --> 00:00:50,190
Excuse me?
You mean, in Yu Na's room?

21
00:00:57,960 --> 00:00:59,100
Of course.

22
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,800
That would be better
for everyone, yes.

23
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:03,700
This way, please.

24
00:01:08,410 --> 00:01:11,280
For goodness' sake.

25
00:01:13,610 --> 00:01:14,610
Oh, dear.

26
00:01:21,220 --> 00:01:22,320
Goodness.

27
00:01:24,220 --> 00:01:25,890
Please wait here for a moment.

28
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:28,460
I'll go get you some fruit.

29
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:30,560
Honey.

30
00:01:31,830 --> 00:01:33,630
Could you get some fruit ready?

31
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:13,540
What do you think you're doing?

32
00:02:25,050 --> 00:02:26,950
It's bad enough you're snooping
around my empty room.

33
00:02:27,450 --> 00:02:29,090
What were you doing with my clothes?

34
00:02:30,460 --> 00:02:34,160
So you're admitting
this jacket is yours.

35
00:02:35,990 --> 00:02:39,700
This is what the design book thief
was wearing in the security footage.

36
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,340
Like this is one of a kind.

37
00:02:47,070 --> 00:02:48,140
Besides,

38
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:50,740
maybe you should check the news
before making accusations.

39
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:54,050
The thief already
confessed publicly.

40
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:58,180
The news? A confession?

41
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:13,430
I'm sorry.

42
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:19,640
I happened to be inside
the Adele Group building...

43
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:22,240
and thought stealing the design book
and streaming it...

44
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:25,010
would create a lot of buzz,
so I did.

45
00:03:26,740 --> 00:03:29,680
I sincerely apologize
and beg for your leniency.

46
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,160
Do you get it now?

47
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:40,690
Stop accusing an innocent person,
and give me back my jacket.

48
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:01,650
But that confession video
just now...

49
00:04:04,850 --> 00:04:05,850
It's a lie.

50
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:07,890
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

51
00:04:15,190 --> 00:04:16,830
That guy's a lefty.

52
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:21,070
But the one who took the design book
was clearly...

53
00:04:23,130 --> 00:04:24,300
They were right-handed.

54
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:27,810
Which means the person
who stole the design book...

55
00:04:28,840 --> 00:04:30,510
and orchestrated
this whole thing is...

56
00:04:44,490 --> 00:04:45,890
- What the...
- What?

57
00:04:46,090 --> 00:04:48,330
What is going on here?

58
00:04:48,330 --> 00:04:49,760
What is this?

59
00:04:55,630 --> 00:04:58,740
Looks like our dear president
has taken a liking to my jacket.

60
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:01,670
Really?
Why would she want your jacket?

61
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:03,740
There's been a misunderstanding.

62
00:05:04,410 --> 00:05:07,780
The closet door opened,
and her clothes came tumbling out.

63
00:05:08,780 --> 00:05:12,320
That's my fault.
I was in a rush and stuffed them in.

64
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:16,520
Right.
I was just trying to put them away,

65
00:05:17,090 --> 00:05:18,890
but then I noticed this jacket
was packed separately.

66
00:05:20,390 --> 00:05:24,030
It looked like the jacket
the design book thief was wearing,

67
00:05:24,830 --> 00:05:26,060
so I took a closer look.

68
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:29,930
What? Are you saying...

69
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:33,570
Are you calling Yu Na a thief?

70
00:05:34,140 --> 00:05:35,540
The nerve!

71
00:05:35,810 --> 00:05:38,510
You call off the wedding,

72
00:05:38,510 --> 00:05:40,210
show up
without a single word of apology,

73
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:43,150
and now you dare treat my daughter
like a thief?

74
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:45,720
Honey, come on. Calm down.

75
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:48,690
We're going to be family, remember?
We'll be in-laws.

76
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:51,190
In-laws, my foot.

77
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:53,420
That wedding was called off
ages ago!

78
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:55,790
I agree completely.

79
00:05:55,860 --> 00:05:57,560
What did you say?

80
00:05:57,700 --> 00:05:59,360
The engagement's off,

81
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,700
so I suggest we move on
like it never happened.

82
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:03,970
Says who?

83
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,500
The chairman...

84
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,970
Min Jun doesn't want this marriage.

85
00:06:08,140 --> 00:06:10,540
I'll convince the chairman myself,

86
00:06:11,110 --> 00:06:13,910
so I hope you can come
to terms with it, Ms. Choi.

87
00:06:17,550 --> 00:06:20,820
You're going to regret
this decision.

88
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:23,150
Will I?

89
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:25,490
I really don't think I will.

90
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:31,000
My goodness.

91
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:34,430
Seriously. You know what? Fine!

92
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,770
We've had enough of this.

93
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:39,800
Let's just call it quits for good!

94
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,810
- What are you talking about?
- Goodness.

95
00:06:41,870 --> 00:06:43,710
I'm marrying him no matter what.

96
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,380
Are you kidding me?

97
00:06:46,910 --> 00:06:48,750
I can't believe this.

98
00:06:50,210 --> 00:06:51,220
Unbelievable.

99
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,590
Were you able to confirm it?

100
00:07:01,690 --> 00:07:03,630
I had a hunch, and I was right.

101
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,530
So Ms. Choi is the one
who stole the design book...

102
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:09,670
and started all this?

103
00:07:13,170 --> 00:07:14,540
How could she?

104
00:07:14,970 --> 00:07:17,980
She did this to get in our way
because the engagement was ending.

105
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,410
Let's report her
to the police right now...

106
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:22,480
and teach her a lesson.

107
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:25,380
Before we do that,
there's something I need to confirm,

108
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:27,080
and I have a few things to prepare.

109
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:40,460
(Adele)

110
00:07:47,670 --> 00:07:49,670
Did you watch the confession video?

111
00:07:50,310 --> 00:07:52,010
Yes, but...

112
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,740
- I think it's fake.
- It's a lie.

113
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,820
The thief in the security footage
was right-handed.

114
00:08:01,950 --> 00:08:04,490
But the person in the video
is left-handed.

115
00:08:05,420 --> 00:08:07,330
So we both noticed the same thing.

116
00:08:11,330 --> 00:08:14,530
I assume you're here
about the confession video.

117
00:08:21,340 --> 00:08:24,280
So Choi Yu Na stole
the design book...

118
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:26,080
and put him up to making
the false accusation?

119
00:08:27,380 --> 00:08:28,780
It's looking that way.

120
00:08:29,780 --> 00:08:31,120
Have you told the police?

121
00:08:31,980 --> 00:08:33,520
Something's bothering me.

122
00:08:34,390 --> 00:08:36,050
Is it the confession video?

123
00:08:38,160 --> 00:08:40,290
The first video accusing me of theft
is one thing,

124
00:08:40,660 --> 00:08:43,160
but the confession video seems off.

125
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:48,700
There's no reason for him to lie
and take the fall for everything.

126
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,640
It could be about the money.

127
00:08:51,540 --> 00:08:54,340
I checked out
his neighborhood today,

128
00:08:55,370 --> 00:08:56,770
and it looked like
he was desperate for cash.

129
00:09:00,110 --> 00:09:04,050
It'd be a relief if Yu Na paid him
for a false confession.

130
00:09:04,220 --> 00:09:08,020
But if he was coerced
because he's in danger,

131
00:09:08,090 --> 00:09:09,850
we can't guarantee his safety.

132
00:09:11,920 --> 00:09:15,260
She'll try to silence
her most crucial witness.

133
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:35,350
I did everything you told me to.

134
00:09:35,750 --> 00:09:36,910
Please, let me go.

135
00:09:38,820 --> 00:09:42,490
Why? So you can run to the cops
and spill your guts?

136
00:09:44,060 --> 00:09:46,420
- No.
- Don't lie to me.

137
00:09:49,890 --> 00:09:52,530
You'll be going down for this alone.

138
00:09:52,830 --> 00:09:54,170
Why wouldn't you admit...

139
00:09:54,330 --> 00:09:56,070
that you were hired to lie,
kidnapped,

140
00:09:56,330 --> 00:09:57,700
and threatened?

141
00:09:58,740 --> 00:10:01,110
I'll just take the fall.

142
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:09,110
Sure. Maybe you want
to take the fall.

143
00:10:09,450 --> 00:10:10,920
But what about
that big mouth of yours?

144
00:10:11,580 --> 00:10:13,850
The second you walk out that door,
you'll feel wronged,

145
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:16,520
and you'll start blabbing
about everything.

146
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:19,290
There's no way
you're walking out of here...

147
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:21,560
with that mouth of yours intact.

148
00:10:22,060 --> 00:10:23,060
Right?

149
00:10:41,950 --> 00:10:43,080
Either way,

150
00:10:43,410 --> 00:10:45,120
finding him has to be our priority.

151
00:10:45,350 --> 00:10:46,520
Like you said,

152
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:50,420
he's our key witness
in proving Ms. Choi is guilty.

153
00:10:51,490 --> 00:10:55,290
Right. I'll ask the police to focus
their investigation on finding him.

154
00:10:57,060 --> 00:10:58,700
What will you do about Choi Yu Na?

155
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:03,700
- Well...
- Why don't we handle her ourselves?

156
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:07,170
The police have their limits,
but we...

157
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,840
could even lay a small trap.

158
00:11:10,780 --> 00:11:12,380
A small trap?

159
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:16,510
We don't have enough evidence
right now.

160
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:20,520
The confession video being a fake
is just our word against hers,

161
00:11:20,950 --> 00:11:24,820
and we can't prove
she stole the design book.

162
00:11:25,390 --> 00:11:28,460
But if we create an opening
and bait her,

163
00:11:29,090 --> 00:11:32,060
we might be able to get
some conclusive evidence.

164
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:33,430
What if...

165
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:36,630
she tries to get rid of something
she used in the crime?

166
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:40,470
Is that the kind of evidence
you mean, Chloe?

167
00:11:52,580 --> 00:11:54,690
I even gave up Dad's shares
to make this all go away.

168
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:58,060
The fake confession was meant to be
the end of it.

169
00:12:00,290 --> 00:12:04,060
I never thought President Kim
would search my room.

170
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:09,170
What if she says something
to the police?

171
00:12:17,780 --> 00:12:19,680
(Clothing Donations)

172
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:21,350
I should've gotten rid
of this sooner.

173
00:12:23,810 --> 00:12:24,880
It's done.

174
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,750
Now there's no evidence left.

175
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:41,130
Dan Hui was right as always.

176
00:12:41,900 --> 00:12:43,630
She got rid of the evidence
right away.

177
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:47,710
That's it, Ms. Choi.
You're so busted.

178
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:53,410
I'll watch Ms. Choi...

179
00:12:53,410 --> 00:12:56,180
while the police look
for the broadcaster,

180
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:59,520
so Chloe, focus on your work
at the company.

181
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:02,650
With the rebranding,
we've got a new product launch...

182
00:13:02,690 --> 00:13:05,120
and an ad campaign.
We have a lot to do, you know.

183
00:13:05,220 --> 00:13:08,460
No. I'm in this with you.

184
00:13:09,330 --> 00:13:12,900
I want to make one thing very clear
to Ms. Choi.

185
00:13:14,030 --> 00:13:16,200
That when you commit a crime,

186
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,040
you will always pay the price.

187
00:13:23,270 --> 00:13:25,340
And don't worry about work.

188
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:28,210
I'm making sure everything
stays on schedule.

189
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:32,380
I'll help Chloe.

190
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:37,660
I'll help her handle
both her work and this case.

191
00:13:53,870 --> 00:13:55,210
I don't need your help.

192
00:13:57,540 --> 00:14:00,340
I can handle it all myself.

193
00:14:01,180 --> 00:14:03,250
Rather than being lost like today...

194
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:04,320
Have you had...

195
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,250
dinner?

196
00:14:09,690 --> 00:14:11,260
Here you go!

197
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:13,890
You're having a pretty late dinner.

198
00:14:14,390 --> 00:14:17,700
Yes. But thanks to you,
we can at least eat.

199
00:14:18,160 --> 00:14:20,330
You should make sure you eat well,
especially when you're busy.

200
00:14:21,030 --> 00:14:24,030
Since it's your second visit,
I made you a big portion, so dig in.

201
00:14:24,870 --> 00:14:26,200
You remember me?

202
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:28,640
Of course. You were here
on your first day at Adele.

203
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:30,040
How could I forget?

204
00:14:30,670 --> 00:14:34,850
I know this is a cafe,
but our tteokbokki is our specialty.

205
00:14:35,810 --> 00:14:37,180
Please try some before it gets cold.

206
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:52,330
Their drinks are good,
but the food is really good too.

207
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,200
Take a bite.

208
00:15:08,810 --> 00:15:11,120
Why haven't you asked me...

209
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:14,180
about the fire yesterday?

210
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:17,660
Because it seems
like a sensitive subject.

211
00:15:21,890 --> 00:15:25,430
It feels like a sore subject
for both of us,

212
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:28,370
so I've been avoiding it.

213
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:31,470
Is that cowardly of me again?

214
00:15:34,870 --> 00:15:37,570
It's not a very painful memory
for me.

215
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:41,850
There was a fire when I was a kid,
and ever since,

216
00:15:42,580 --> 00:15:43,580
fires make me uneasy.

217
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:46,920
It's like being afraid of dogs
or hating bugs.

218
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,220
Something like that.

219
00:15:49,620 --> 00:15:54,590
But why is it
such a sensitive subject for you?

220
00:16:02,530 --> 00:16:05,770
She must have been in so much pain
during that fire.

221
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:10,540
She shouldn't still be feeling
that pain, wherever she is now.

222
00:16:11,980 --> 00:16:13,540
That's what I worry about.

223
00:16:15,380 --> 00:16:18,550
I lost the person I loved in a fire,
you see.

224
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:30,560
That's why, when I see your pain,

225
00:16:31,330 --> 00:16:32,400
I can't help but wonder if,

226
00:16:33,330 --> 00:16:35,270
by some one-in-a-million chance...

227
00:16:37,230 --> 00:16:39,340
I end up with nothing
but wishful thinking.

228
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:49,080
What about the police?

229
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:50,910
What?

230
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:54,250
They'll put him
on the no-fly list...

231
00:16:54,790 --> 00:16:55,890
and search for him?

232
00:16:56,890 --> 00:17:00,460
Darn. Then why don't we
just catch the punk ourselves?

233
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,500
I see.

234
00:17:09,100 --> 00:17:10,130
Then again,

235
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:13,470
now that it's been exposed
as a false accusation,

236
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:17,880
we don't need to waste manpower
on catching one lousy thief.

237
00:17:19,480 --> 00:17:20,480
Hey.

238
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:24,650
The Adele Group is the victim here.
Got it?

239
00:17:25,150 --> 00:17:27,750
Just spin it that way going forward.

240
00:17:28,490 --> 00:17:29,490
Exactly.

241
00:17:32,590 --> 00:17:35,990
Why can't you just step in
and catch the thief yourself?

242
00:17:37,900 --> 00:17:38,900
Why would I do that?

243
00:17:39,530 --> 00:17:42,170
Come on.
You're not going to forgive him...

244
00:17:42,230 --> 00:17:43,700
just because
of his confession video, are you?

245
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:47,070
It's bad enough if he stole
from one of our offices,

246
00:17:47,070 --> 00:17:50,670
but it's even worse if he's lying
to cover for someone else.

247
00:17:51,780 --> 00:17:54,510
Isn't it best to punish whoever
is responsible as soon as possible?

248
00:17:54,580 --> 00:17:56,180
If we catch him right away,

249
00:17:57,380 --> 00:18:00,420
he'll just go to prison
and sleep soundly.

250
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:03,090
But the longer he avoids capture,

251
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:06,420
the more he'll suffer as a fugitive.

252
00:18:08,260 --> 00:18:10,530
We'll back the thief
into a corner first.

253
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:14,970
We'll have time to punish
whoever is responsible later. Okay?

254
00:18:18,040 --> 00:18:20,770
Unbelievable. You're no help at all.

255
00:18:24,310 --> 00:18:25,510
No way.

256
00:18:26,180 --> 00:18:27,580
Mad respect.

257
00:18:28,210 --> 00:18:30,950
He's not just going to catch him,
he's going to torture him first.

258
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,350
Man, I've got to hand it
to Chairman Park.

259
00:18:35,090 --> 00:18:38,420
Maybe I should've just hinted
that Choi Yu Na was behind this.

260
00:18:38,690 --> 00:18:40,020
That confession video...

261
00:18:40,390 --> 00:18:43,160
My gut is telling me he's lying.

262
00:18:46,330 --> 00:18:48,500
Hi, son.

263
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,370
You're off work already?

264
00:18:51,070 --> 00:18:53,400
I left right on time.
My policy is to clock out on time.

265
00:18:53,470 --> 00:18:56,740
That's right.
Only work what you're paid for.

266
00:18:57,270 --> 00:18:59,610
You're Adele's heir,
the future owner.

267
00:18:59,610 --> 00:19:00,710
Don't overwork yourself.

268
00:19:00,810 --> 00:19:03,380
Leave all the hard stuff to me.

269
00:19:03,910 --> 00:19:06,450
If I left it to you,
things would get even worse.

270
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:09,020
Why would you say that?

271
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:12,520
As a matter of fact,
I just fixed a complicated mess.

272
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:16,660
I've paved a smooth, easy path
for your future.

273
00:19:17,230 --> 00:19:19,300
Right, and I'll be sure
to avoid that path...

274
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:23,430
Wait, why didn't I think of that?

275
00:19:24,940 --> 00:19:25,940
Where's Mr. Song?

276
00:19:26,940 --> 00:19:28,740
Why are you suddenly
looking for him?

277
00:19:29,470 --> 00:19:31,640
I need something from him.

278
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:33,780
Don't bother looking for him.

279
00:19:34,910 --> 00:19:37,250
I sent him on an errand,
so he won't be back for a few days.

280
00:19:37,310 --> 00:19:41,020
A few days? What? Why?
Where? What errand?

281
00:19:41,690 --> 00:19:46,320
I'm so tired. I must be getting old.

282
00:19:46,390 --> 00:19:47,390
Wait.

283
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:50,190
- Goodness.
- What the...

284
00:19:57,870 --> 00:20:01,840
What... Darn it.

285
00:20:07,710 --> 00:20:09,280
Untie me already!

286
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:13,320
I was dumb to trust
that crazy old bat.

287
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:15,650
- Crazy?
- Gosh.

288
00:20:22,690 --> 00:20:25,200
- Why did you hit me?
- Crazy old bat?

289
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:27,800
She might be crazy,
and yes, she's old,

290
00:20:28,230 --> 00:20:30,830
but I won't let some punk like you
insult her!

291
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:36,870
There are two people in the world
I hold dearer than my own life.

292
00:20:37,010 --> 00:20:39,610
One's the "crazy old bat"
you insulted,

293
00:20:39,610 --> 00:20:41,380
and the other one is...

294
00:20:57,690 --> 00:21:00,300
Hey. Why are you calling me
at this hour?

295
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:04,100
Did something happen
to your mom or you?

296
00:21:04,230 --> 00:21:06,270
Where are you? Do you need me there?

297
00:21:07,940 --> 00:21:09,710
Why is he being so dramatic?

298
00:21:11,980 --> 00:21:14,540
No, nothing's wrong.
I'm calling about something else.

299
00:21:14,610 --> 00:21:16,910
Something else? What is it?

300
00:21:17,180 --> 00:21:18,180
Mr. Song.

301
00:21:18,550 --> 00:21:21,150
You heard about the false accusation
against our company, right?

302
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:24,050
Yes, of course...

303
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:27,320
Of course I know.

304
00:21:27,660 --> 00:21:30,260
I want to find the guy
who made the false accusation.

305
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:33,200
What? Why?

306
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:36,130
So we can catch him
and punish him, of course.

307
00:21:36,570 --> 00:21:39,140
But it seems like Chairman Park
and Ms. Oh...

308
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,470
won't be much help.

309
00:21:40,770 --> 00:21:43,640
You're the only one I can trust
to handle this.

310
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:46,680
The one you can trust
to handle this...

311
00:21:48,180 --> 00:21:49,180
is me?

312
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:50,850
That's right.

313
00:21:52,350 --> 00:21:53,420
You'll find him for me, right?

314
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:54,750
Of course!

315
00:21:57,490 --> 00:21:59,690
About that...

316
00:22:01,090 --> 00:22:03,030
Is that a yes or a no?

317
00:22:03,390 --> 00:22:06,530
Well, it's...

318
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:09,900
If you can't, never mind.
All right, I'm hanging up.

319
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:16,110
Wait, hello? Hello?

320
00:22:18,180 --> 00:22:21,480
He said I was the only one
he could trust.

321
00:22:22,410 --> 00:22:24,820
But why...

322
00:22:26,480 --> 00:22:29,220
did he have to look for this punk?

323
00:22:32,590 --> 00:22:34,320
Let's just die together!

324
00:22:35,260 --> 00:22:39,630
(Adele)

325
00:22:43,170 --> 00:22:44,800
My gosh!

326
00:22:45,940 --> 00:22:48,070
- Good morning.
- You scared me.

327
00:22:50,110 --> 00:22:51,680
What brings you to the office?

328
00:22:52,380 --> 00:22:56,050
My dear Chloe is going through
a tough time.

329
00:22:56,150 --> 00:22:59,250
I was so worried that I decided
to come in with her.

330
00:22:59,650 --> 00:23:01,750
What's in there...

331
00:23:02,890 --> 00:23:04,590
that's got your attention?

332
00:23:08,830 --> 00:23:11,090
You'll find out in due time.

333
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:14,360
For now,
this is strictly confidential.

334
00:23:14,530 --> 00:23:15,600
Now, if you'll excuse me.

335
00:23:18,140 --> 00:23:19,770
What do you think you're doing?

336
00:23:19,770 --> 00:23:22,410
Ms. Jung, I'm truly hurt.

337
00:23:22,770 --> 00:23:26,810
I thought we bonded
after what happened in that alley.

338
00:23:27,110 --> 00:23:29,650
Just give me a hint
about what I'll find out later.

339
00:23:30,010 --> 00:23:33,680
We might be comrades-in-arms,
but security is security.

340
00:23:47,130 --> 00:23:50,230
Your face is suddenly
turning beet red.

341
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:52,600
Don't tell me...

342
00:23:57,040 --> 00:24:00,440
It's not what you think.
Really, it's not.

343
00:24:01,010 --> 00:24:04,150
As if. I can tell just by looking.

344
00:24:06,620 --> 00:24:07,680
This is...

345
00:24:08,850 --> 00:24:09,920
definitely...

346
00:24:10,290 --> 00:24:11,290
Yes?

347
00:24:14,220 --> 00:24:15,530
It's male menopause.

348
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:18,860
Male menopause?

349
00:24:19,630 --> 00:24:21,830
You should go take care of yourself.

350
00:24:22,370 --> 00:24:24,200
I'm busy, so I'll be on my way.

351
00:24:28,940 --> 00:24:30,670
I'm not going through
male menopause!

352
00:24:31,040 --> 00:24:34,910
I'm a young man in his prime,
you hear?

353
00:24:35,310 --> 00:24:37,980
Come on. Look at these guns.

354
00:24:43,390 --> 00:24:45,220
(Consultant, Chloe Lee)

355
00:24:46,290 --> 00:24:48,630
You watched the confession video,
didn't you?

356
00:24:49,660 --> 00:24:51,960
Don't you think
you owe me an apology?

357
00:24:52,930 --> 00:24:54,260
How dare you...

358
00:24:54,930 --> 00:24:56,700
accuse me of being a thief?

359
00:24:58,130 --> 00:24:59,140
I don't know about that.

360
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:01,640
It seems a bit too soon
for an apology.

361
00:25:02,310 --> 00:25:05,980
There may still be more
to the story.

362
00:25:11,820 --> 00:25:13,020
Ms. Choi.

363
00:25:16,450 --> 00:25:17,590
What are you doing here?

364
00:25:18,120 --> 00:25:19,120
What is this about?

365
00:25:19,420 --> 00:25:20,760
You tell me.

366
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:26,600
Why do you think I'm here?

367
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:31,900
Let's go discuss this
over a cup of tea.

368
00:25:36,910 --> 00:25:38,780
Wait, isn't she...

369
00:25:40,340 --> 00:25:41,910
But why is she here for Yu Na?

370
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:54,690
Get your hands off me. Let go.

371
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:01,900
You can't just show up
at work like this.

372
00:26:02,630 --> 00:26:05,340
That's exactly what a debtor
would say.

373
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,570
So you do admit
you owe me something.

374
00:26:08,870 --> 00:26:10,110
Did I say I wasn't going
to give it to you?

375
00:26:10,610 --> 00:26:12,410
Why are you pushing me like this?

376
00:26:12,410 --> 00:26:13,980
Exactly.

377
00:26:15,710 --> 00:26:18,150
You should've brought it to me
without me having to ask.

378
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:21,250
I need some time
to get everything together.

379
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:22,920
Get everything together?

380
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:24,990
I've already taken care of it.

381
00:26:26,390 --> 00:26:29,260
The shares are
in your father's name, right?

382
00:26:29,790 --> 00:26:32,300
I've got the power of attorney
and transfer papers ready,

383
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:35,200
so just bring your father's seal.

384
00:26:36,230 --> 00:26:38,130
If you try anything
and drag your feet,

385
00:26:38,940 --> 00:26:41,270
I'll tell the chairman
as soon as he's off work.

386
00:26:42,340 --> 00:26:45,810
Stop scheming and get to work.

387
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:06,930
Wait, what's going on?
Why do you need my official seal?

388
00:27:07,160 --> 00:27:09,100
This is urgent,
so I'll fill you in later.

389
00:27:10,170 --> 00:27:15,240
Urgent or not, you don't just give
your seal away, not even to family.

390
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:16,910
I have to know what it's for...

391
00:27:16,910 --> 00:27:18,340
I'm your daughter!

392
00:27:18,910 --> 00:27:20,080
Can't you just give it to me?

393
00:27:20,540 --> 00:27:21,540
Choi Yu Na.

394
00:27:26,220 --> 00:27:29,490
I need it to transfer your shares.
There, are you happy?

395
00:27:30,190 --> 00:27:31,920
What? Transfer my shares?

396
00:27:32,490 --> 00:27:33,660
You mean you're selling them?

397
00:27:34,390 --> 00:27:36,890
- To who?
- For now, I'm signing them over.

398
00:27:37,660 --> 00:27:40,060
I'll get them back later,
so don't worry about it.

399
00:27:40,700 --> 00:27:43,430
Hey! Yu Na, wait!

400
00:27:44,100 --> 00:27:46,800
What in the world
is she talking about?

401
00:27:47,970 --> 00:27:50,270
Other than this house,
that's the only asset we have left.

402
00:27:50,970 --> 00:27:53,340
Who on earth could she
be signing them over to?

403
00:27:54,610 --> 00:27:56,350
And how does she plan
to get them back later?

404
00:27:58,250 --> 00:28:01,120
Wait a minute.
She can get them back?

405
00:28:02,890 --> 00:28:05,690
Does she mean
after she gets married?

406
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:09,660
Is she trading my stocks
for her wedding?

407
00:28:10,290 --> 00:28:12,560
What am I going to do?

408
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:15,200
Goodness, what's going on?

409
00:28:15,670 --> 00:28:18,200
Why was Yu Na here
during work hours?

410
00:28:18,770 --> 00:28:21,740
Goodness, what's with
that look on your face?

411
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:24,610
- Honey, it's Yu Na.
- Yes?

412
00:28:24,610 --> 00:28:26,080
I think she's...

413
00:28:27,310 --> 00:28:30,950
This is torture.
Cat got your tongue?

414
00:28:31,010 --> 00:28:32,650
Just spit it out.

415
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:34,920
- Well...
- Yes?

416
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:37,620
Yu Na ran off with my seal.

417
00:28:37,620 --> 00:28:39,920
What, your seal?

418
00:28:40,490 --> 00:28:41,930
What would she want with it?

419
00:28:43,290 --> 00:28:47,600
She's not in her right mind
since her engagement was called off.

420
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,570
I think she's planning
to sign over our stocks...

421
00:28:50,130 --> 00:28:52,340
to get their approval
for the marriage.

422
00:28:52,900 --> 00:28:54,900
What did you just say?

423
00:28:56,110 --> 00:28:59,640
My gosh. That's just absurd!

424
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:02,050
Those scoundrels have
another thing coming.

425
00:29:02,780 --> 00:29:04,410
- Unbelievable.
- Honey, wait!

426
00:29:05,250 --> 00:29:08,890
What now? What do we do about this?

427
00:29:09,490 --> 00:29:11,490
You've got to be kidding me.

428
00:29:16,390 --> 00:29:18,800
Just like you said, she tried
to get rid of the evidence.

429
00:29:19,460 --> 00:29:21,530
I made sure to get it all on video.

430
00:29:22,330 --> 00:29:25,070
I think we can use that
as evidence against Ms. Choi.

431
00:29:25,540 --> 00:29:28,510
(BIT Life, President Kim Myung Hui)

432
00:29:36,010 --> 00:29:37,710
The police don't have any leads yet.

433
00:29:37,980 --> 00:29:39,750
Since the confession video aired,

434
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:42,620
there have been no signs of him,
so he's hard to track.

435
00:29:43,620 --> 00:29:46,960
There's been no cellphone
or credit card activity at all.

436
00:29:49,830 --> 00:29:53,600
Where is everyone?
Get out here, now!

437
00:29:53,830 --> 00:29:58,230
I'm going to settle this
once and for all today.

438
00:29:58,330 --> 00:29:59,440
What is this?

439
00:29:59,440 --> 00:30:00,470
Let go of me.

440
00:30:00,470 --> 00:30:02,240
What brings you all the way here?

441
00:30:04,340 --> 00:30:07,240
Yesterday, you treated my daughter
like a thief,

442
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:09,480
and now you're actually
turning her into one.

443
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:11,480
What are you talking about?

444
00:30:11,580 --> 00:30:15,750
I know my Yu Na is head over heels
for this punk, but still.

445
00:30:16,850 --> 00:30:20,090
How dare you use her feelings
to try and snatch up our stocks?

446
00:30:22,630 --> 00:30:26,000
Yu Na ran off
with my husband's seal...

447
00:30:26,700 --> 00:30:28,500
to hand over our shares to you.

448
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:30,900
You two are teaming up to ruin us.

449
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:34,440
Ms. Choi is signing over
your shares?

450
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:38,880
(Stock Transfer Agreement)

451
00:30:44,910 --> 00:30:46,320
(Grantor: Choi Sam Sik)

452
00:30:49,090 --> 00:30:50,390
(Grantor: Choi Sam Sik)

453
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:56,030
(Grantor: Choi Sam Sik)

454
00:30:58,390 --> 00:31:00,030
(Grantor: Choi Sam Sik)

455
00:31:20,620 --> 00:31:21,650
You...

456
00:31:22,290 --> 00:31:24,750
What do you think you're doing?

457
00:32:05,930 --> 00:32:08,930
(Pearl in Red)

458
00:32:09,270 --> 00:32:11,070
That miserable tramp.

459
00:32:11,230 --> 00:32:12,870
How did she find out
and track us down...

460
00:32:12,870 --> 00:32:13,900
just to ruin everything?

461
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:16,070
Pull yourselves together.

462
00:32:16,070 --> 00:32:19,140
I make all the decisions
in this family. Period.

463
00:32:19,310 --> 00:32:21,280
As long as I back Ms. Choi,

464
00:32:21,910 --> 00:32:23,250
the wedding will happen,

465
00:32:23,250 --> 00:32:26,180
and I'll get her father's shares.

466
00:32:26,320 --> 00:32:29,690
If she's really keeping him
locked up like you said, ma'am,

467
00:32:30,420 --> 00:32:32,890
wouldn't he be in serious trouble?

468
00:32:33,060 --> 00:32:36,030
Wait, you're changing the whole plan
because you didn't get the stocks?

469
00:32:36,330 --> 00:32:39,600
Please don't tell me
you're planning to kill again.

470
00:32:40,730 --> 00:32:42,730
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
